Compute the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a matrix.

Eigenvalues are computed in a several step process which begins with a
Hessenberg decomposition, followed by a Schur@tie{}decomposition, from which
the eigenvalues are apparent.  The eigenvectors, when desired, are computed
by further manipulations of the Schur@tie{}decomposition.

The eigenvalues returned by @code{eig} are not ordered.
@seealso{@ref{doc-eigs,,eigs}, @ref{doc-svd,,svd}}
@end deftypefn


